  // NED ORIGIN vs TERRAIN NOTE
  // AirSim sets NED Z=0 at the Unreal PlayerStart actor.  If PlayerStart is
  // placed above the terrain mesh in the Unreal level, the visual floor will
  // appear at some positive NED Z (= terrain_offset_m below PlayerStart).
  // All L0 obstacle evidence is correctly positioned in NED — obstacle
  // avoidance is unaffected.  The only symptom is visual: evidence that
  // correctly sits on the floor appears to "float" above the AirSim rendered
  // ground when the viewer draws a ground plane at NED Z=0.
  //
  // Fix option A (preferred): open the Unreal project, select PlayerStart in
  // the World Outliner, press End to snap it to the terrain surface, save.
  //
  // Fix option B (settings.json): set the vehicle spawn Z to the terrain
  // offset so the drone spawns at NED Z = terrain_offset_m (at terrain level).
  // Measure terrain_offset_m by arming the drone and reading
  // local_T_body.position.z from the world_snapshot SSE stream while sitting
  // on the ground; that value IS terrain_offset_m.  Then set Z below.
  // (AirSim NED: positive Z = down; 8.0 = 8 m below PlayerStart.)
  //
  "Z": 8.0,   // <-- set to measured terrain_offset_m 

